        [
          "Sequential Pattern Mining",
          "Higher Education",
          "Blended Learning",
          "104 students",
          "1 Digitizing Cultural Heritage course",
          "LMS logs, Student Reflection",
          "Adaption of 3 Common SRL Models",
          "[Goal Setting, Making Personal Plans, Working on a Task, Reformulation, Evaluation, Reflection]",
          "Authors take logs and associate different activities as part of wider SRL constructs. In total, there were 63716 logged events, out of which 48602 were labelled. \n\n ",
          "cSPADE",
          "Mininum support of 0.40 and minimum confidence of 0.6.",
          "2",
          "High PErforming Students:\n\nStudents tended to reflect more on their SRL behaviors. Specifically, these students have a higher proneness of Reformulation→ Reflection than their peers. \n\nLow-Performing Students\n\nLess prone to reflect on their SRL behaviours. \n\n",
          "High performance students are often better at planning and reflecting their peers.\n\nLow performing students often focus on fulfilling academic obligations rather than promoting their work and development.\n\nInstructors can provide specific prompts to “force” their students to reflect more on their SRL behaviors. \n\n",
          "Authors use Sequential Pattern mining to identify different transitions of learning behavior. \n\n",
          "Only uses one very general course. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
